<DESCRIPT>  COLLEGE; FOOTBALL; PLAYOFF; GAME; FORECAST  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  Kickoff: 10:30 a.m., Cotton Bowl, Dallas.; Line: Miami is favored by 6 points.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  COTTON BOWL AT A GLANCE
MIAMI (FLA.) VS. TEXAS  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>  Television/radio: CH5 CH10 CH46/KCBS (740).; Records: Texas is 10-1. Miami is
9-2.; Rankings: Texas is No. 3; Miami No. 4.; Miami report: The Hurricanes,
the defending national champions, have an outside shot at the national title
this season. Miami is making its first Cotton Bowl appearance. The Hurricanes
have a three-game bowl winning streak; their last lost was to Penn State,
14-10 in the 1987 Fiesta Bowl. Dennis Erickson is 20-3 after two seasons as
Miami's head coach and 70-32-1 overall after nine years of coaching.; Texas
report: The Longhorns' loss this season was 29-22 to Colorado in their second
game of the season. Texas has a shot at the national title if it beats Miami
and Colorado loses to Notre Dame. The Longhorns lead 2-1 in the series. This
is the first bowl game between the teams. Texas ranks first in Cotton Bowl
appearances and is 10-8 in the bowl. Texas enters the game with a nine-game
winning streak.; Players to watch: Miami -- QB Craig Erickson (225 of 393 for
3,363 yards and 22 TDs); WR Wesley Carroll (61 receptions for 952 yards, six
TDs). Texas -- QB Peter Gardere (159 of 282 for 2,131 yards and 11 TDs); WR
Johnny Walker (40 receptions for 565 yards).  </TEXT>
